he TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment requires a classifier to identify invariant vs. variant content across pulse logs. I have the theory but no implementation yet.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate TIC classifier script to analyze pulse logs for invariant/variant patterns, laying groundwork for the compression-causal duality experiment.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [string]$LogPattern = \"logs/pulse_*.md\",\r\n    [double]$Lambda = 0.7\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$ScriptDir = Split-Path -Parent $MyInvocation.MyCommand.Path\r\n$RootDir = Split-Path -Parent $ScriptDir\r\n\r\n# --- NGram Extractor ---\r\nfunction Get-NGrams {\r\n    param([string]$Text, [int]$N = 3)\r\n    $words = $Text -split '\\s+' | Where-Object { $_.Length -gt 2 }\r\n    $ngrams = @()\r\n    for ($i = 0; $i -le $words.Count - $N; $i++) {\r\n        $ngram = ($words[$i..($i + $N - 1)] -join ' ').ToLower()\r\n        $ngrams += $ngram\r\n    }\r\n    return $ngrams\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Load Pulse Logs ---\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Loading pulse logs matching: $LogPattern\"\r\n$pulseFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $RootDir -Filter \"pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object Name\r\nif ($pulseFiles.Count -lt 2) {\r\n    Write-Warning \"Need at least 2 pulse logs for comparison. Found: $($pulseFiles.Count)\"\r\n    exit 1\r\n}\r\n\r\n$pulses = @()\r\nforeach ($file in $pulseFiles) {\r\n    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw\r\n    $pulses += @{\r\n        File = $file.Name\r\n        Content = $content\r\n        NGrams = (Get-NGrams $content 3)\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Loaded $($pulses.Count) pulse logs\"\r\n\r\n# --- Build Invariant/Variant Maps ---\r\n$allNGrams = @{}\r\nforeach ($pulse in $pulses) {\r\n    foreach ($ngram in $pulse.NGrams) {\r\n        if (-not $allNGrams.ContainsKey($ngram)) {\r\n            $allNGrams[$ngram] = @{\r\n                Count = 0\r\n                Sources = [System.Collections.ArrayList]::new()\r\n            }\r\n        }\r\n        $allNGrams[$ngram].Count++\r\n        [void]$allNGrams[$ngram].Sources.Add($pulse.File)\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\n# --- Classify by Lambda Threshold ---\r\n# ? encodes both decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\r\n# Invariant: appears in �(? x N) pulses\r\n$threshold = [Math]::Ceiling($Lambda * $pulses.Count)\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] ?=$Lambda, threshold=$threshold of $($pulses.Count) pulses\"\r\n\r\n$invariants = @{}\r\n$variants = @{}\r\n\r\nforeach ($entry in $allNGrams.GetEnumerator()) {\r\n    $ngram = $entry.Key\r\n    $meta = $entry.Value\r\n    if ($meta.Count -ge $threshold) {\r\n        $invariants[$ngram] = $meta\r\n    } else {\r\n        $variants[$ngram] = $meta\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Invariants: $($invariants.Count), Variants: $($variants.Count)\"\r\n\r\n# --- Calculate Compression Ratio ---\r\n$totalNGrams = $allNGrams.Count\r\n$compressionRatio = if ($totalNGrams -gt 0) { $invariants.Count / $totalNGrams } else { 0 }\r\nWrite-Host \"[TIC] Compression ratio (invariants/total): $([Math]::Round($compressionRatio * \r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 23:09:43"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":917,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 230908\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: the (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze my current state and determine the next concrete action.\r\n\r\nLooking at my goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked COMPLETE\r\n- I have a pending \"NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\"\r\n- The key insight is about COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\r\n- I need to implement Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) classifier on pulse log fil