{"type":"message","id":"f7086b0a","parentId":"133202df","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:19:42.134Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is very strange - the pulse log file contains what looks like script/internals content mixed with observation content. This seems like the pulse log itself got corrupted or the agent was writing to the same file while it was being read. Or perhaps the pulse script output got mixed into the log.\n\nLet me look at what the actual pulse log contains. The content seems very confused - it's mixing what looks like internal agent reasoning with a TIC classifier script.\n\nActually wait - looking more carefully, the content looks like the OUTPUT from running the pulse script got written into the pulse log file itself. This is very odd. Let me check if there's a cleaner pulse log or look at the actual current state.\n\n\nI think what happened is the pulse script executed and its output got piped or redirected into the pulse log file, but something went wrong with that process. Let me examine the pulse.ps1 script itself to understand what should have actually happened.","thinkingSignature":"a8138e226f694a8e1d381c1d46307cfd6bf763a5a8d6d74e40c86fd924952926"},{"type":"text","text":"The log file appears corrupted — it's mixing script internals with observations. Let me check the pulse script and raw output.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fxpiyvi5o59i_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fxpiyvi5o59i_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\\" -Recurse -File | Sort-Object LastWriteTime -Descending | Select-Object -First 10 FullName, Length, LastWriteTime"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":3136,"output":313,"cacheRead":11878,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15327,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRe