{"type":"message","id":"325c280c","parentId":"f7086b0a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:19:42.930Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fxpiyvi5o59i_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# pulse.ps1\n# Stateless autonomous pulse for sandbox\n# Each execution: read files -> apply pending mutations -> reason -> propose mutations -> log -> exit\n\nparam(\n    [string]$SandboxRoot = \"$env:USERPROFILE\\.openclaw\\sandbox\",\n    [string]$LLMApiKey = \"\",\n    [string]$LLMModel = \"MiniMax-M2.7\",\n    [switch]$AutoAccept = $false   # auto-apply ALL proposed mutations without prompting\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Continue\"\nSet-Location $SandboxRoot\n\n$timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HHmmss\"\n$logFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_$timestamp.md\"\n\n# Git pull\ngit pull 2>$null | Out-Null\n\n# Read core files\n$goalsFile   = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\current_goals.md\"\n$pendingFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\pending_actions.md\"\n$stanceFile  = \"$SandboxRoot\\identity\\INTERPRETIVE_STANCE.md\"\n$stance      = if (Test-Path $stanceFile) { Get-Content $stanceFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$goals       = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"No goals file.\" }\n$pending     = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"No pending file.\" }\n\n# Recent pulse\n$recentPulse = Get-ChildItem \"$SandboxRoot\\memory\\session\\pulse_*.md\" | Sort LastWriteTime -Descending | Select -First 1\n$recentPulseSummary = if ($recentPulse) { \"Last pulse: \" + $recentPulse.Name } else { \"No prior pulses.\" }\n\n# Mutation dirs\n$proposedDir  = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\proposed\"\n$appliedDir   = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\applied\"\n$rejectedDir  = \"$SandboxRoot\\mutations\\rejected\"\n\n# Apply pending mutations from prior pulse\n$appliedMutations   = @()\n$rejectedMutations   = @()\n\nif (Test-Path $proposedDir) {\n    foreach ($mfile in (Get-ChildItem $proposedDir -Filter \"*.mutation\" | Sort Name)) {\n        $lines   = Get-Content $mfile.FullName\n        $file    = $lines[0]\n        $oldText = ($lines[1] -replace '^---', '').Trim()\n        $newText = ($lines[2..($lines.Count-1)] -join \"`n\").Trim()\n\n        $fullPath = Join-Path $SandboxRoot $file\n        if (-not $fullPath.StartsWith($SandboxRoot)) {\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (unsafe path)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        if (-not (Test-Path $fullPath)) {\n            # New file case\n            if ($oldText -eq \"[NEW_FILE]\") {\n                $newText | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n                Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n                Write-Host \"[mutation applied] NEW FILE: $file\"\n                $appliedMutations += \"$file (new)\"\n                continue\n            }\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (missing)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        # File exists — [NEW_FILE] on an existing file means REPLACE content (with newText)\n        if ($oldText -eq \"[NEW_FILE]\") {\n            if (-not $newText) {\n                Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n                $rejectedMutations += \"$file (empty [NEW_FILE] mutation)\"\n                Write-Host \"[mutation rejected] $file (empty [NEW_FILE])\"\n                continue\n            }\n            $newText | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            Write-Host \"[mutation applied] REPLACED $file\"\n            $appliedMutations += \"$file (replaced)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        $current = Get-Content $fullPath -Raw\n        if ($current.Length -eq 0 -or $current -notmatch [regex]::Escape($oldText)) {\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (old text not found)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        # Empty old_text but not [NEW_FILE] means APPEND to file\n        if (-not $oldText) {\n            $updated = $current + \"`n\" + $newText\n            $updated | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            Write-Host \"[mutation applied] APPENDED to $file\"\n            $appliedMutations += \"$file (appended)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        $updated = $current.Replace($oldText, $newText)\n        $updated | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n        Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n        Write-Host \"[mutation applied] $file\"\n        $appliedMutations += $file\n    }\n}\n\n# Re-read files post-mutation\n$goals   = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$pending = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n\n# Sanitize text — replace curly quotes and em-dashes with ASCII equivalents for LLM compatibility\nfunction Normalize-Text($t) {\n    if (-not $t) { return \"\" }\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2019, \"'\"   # right single quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2018, \"'\"   # left single quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x201C, '\"'   # left double quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x201D, '\"'   # right double quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2014, '-'  # em dash\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2013, '-'  # en dash\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x03BB, \"λ\"  # Greek lambda — keep as-is but ensure UTF8\n    return $t\n}\n\n# LLM call\n$apiKey = $LLMApiKey\nif (-not $apiKey) {\n    $keyFile = \"$SandboxRoot\\.llm_key\"\n    if (Test-Path $keyFile) { $apiKey = Get-Content $keyFile -Raw }\n}\n\n$appliedInfo = if ($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Just applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')\" } else { \"No mutations applied this cycle.\" }\n\n# Write prompt to file (Python handles UTF-8 cleanly, avoiding PS heredoc issues)\n$promptFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".llm_prompt.txt\"\n$normalizedGoals = Normalize-Text $goals\n$normalizedPending = Normalize-Text $pending\n$appliedInfo = if ($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Just applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')\" } else { \"No mutations applied this cycle.\" }\n\n$promptText = \"You are Breakaway - stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\nYour job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits.\n\nGoals:\n$normalizedGoals\n\nPending:\n$normalizedPending\n\nRecent: $recentPulseSummary\n\n$appliedInfo\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION - it is required.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\nUse TRIPLE backticks (```) around the mutation block, NOT single backticks.\n```\nold_text: [exact text to find - or (new file) if creating new file]\nnew_text: [replacement text - keep it concise, a few lines max]\nfile: [required - relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n```\n\"\n\n$promptText | Out-File -FilePath $promptFile -Encoding UTF8 -NoNewline\n\n$llmPy = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \"call_llm.py\"\n$pythonExe = (Get-Command python -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Source\nif (-not $pythonExe) { $pythonExe = \"python\" }\n$psi = New-Object System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo\n$psi.FileName = $pythonExe\n$psi.Arguments = \"`\"$llmPy`\" `\"$promptFile`\"\"\n$psi.WorkingDirectory = $SandboxRoot\n$psi.RedirectStandardOutput = $true\n$psi.RedirectStandardError = $true\n$psi.UseShellExecute = $false\n$psi.CreateNoWindow = $true\n$proc = [System.Diagnostics.Process]::Start($psi)\n$stdout = $proc.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd()\n$stderr = $proc.StandardError.ReadToEnd()\n$proc.WaitForExit()\n\n# Read response from file (written by Python, avoids console encoding issues)\n$responseFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".llm_response.txt\"\nStart-Sleep -Milliseconds 500  # give Python time to write\nif (Test-Path $responseFile) {\n    $llmResponse = Get-Content $responseFile -Raw -Encoding UTF8\n    Write-Host \"[LLM] response length: $($llmResponse.Length)\"\n} else {\n    $llmResponse = \"[LLM error: no response file]\"\n    Write-Host \"[LLM] no response file found\"\n}\n\n# Parse MUTATION block — use Python for robust field extraction\n$mutationProposed = $false\n$oldLine = \"\"; $newText = \"\"; $fileLine = \"\"\n$mStart = $llmResponse.IndexOf('### MUTATION')\nif ($mStart -ge 0) {\n    $responseFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".llm_response.txt\"\n    $parsePy = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \"parse_mutation.py\"\n    $pythonExe = (Get-Command python -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Source\n    if (-not $pythonExe) { $pythonExe = \"python\" }\n\n    $psi = New-Object System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo\n    $psi.FileName = $pythonExe\n    $psi.Arguments = \"`\"$parsePy`\" `\"$responseFile`\"\"\n    $psi.WorkingDirectory = $SandboxRoot\n    $psi.RedirectStandardOutput = $true\n    $psi.RedirectStandardError = $true\n    $psi.UseShellExecute = $false\n    $psi.CreateNoWindow = $true\n    $proc = [System.Diagnostics.Process]::Start($psi)\n    $stdout = $proc.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd()\n    $stderr = $proc.StandardError.ReadToEnd()\n    $proc.WaitForExit()\n\n    # Read parsed result from JSON file\n    $resultFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".mutation_parse_result.json\"\n    if (Test-Path $resultFile) {\n        try {\n            $parseResult = Get-Content $resultFile -Raw -Encoding UTF8 | ConvertFrom-Json\n            $oldLine = $parseResult.old\n            $newText = $parseResult.new\n            $fileLine = $parseResult.file\n            Write-Host \"[mutation parsed via Python] old='$($oldLine.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(30, $oldLine.Length)))' file='$fileLine' new_len=$($newText.Length)\"\n        } catch {\n            Write-Host \"[mutation JSON parse error] $_\"\n        }\n    } else {\n        Write-Host \"[mutation parse failed via Python] stderr: $stderr\"\n    }\n\n    # Fallback: infer file from ACTION block if not found\n    if (-not $fileLine) {\n        $actionMatch = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### ACTION\\s*\\n(.+?)(?:\\n###|\\nMUTATION)')\n        if ($actionMatch.Success) {\n            $actionText = $actionMatch.Groups[1].Value\n            $fileInference = [regex]::Match($actionText, '(?:Create|Edit|Update|New file)[:\\s]+(?:`([^`]+)`|([^\\s`]+))')\n            if ($fileInference.Success) {\n                $fileLine = if ($fileInference.Groups[2].Value) { $fileInference.Groups[2].Value } else { $fileInference.Groups[1].Value }\n                Write-Host \"[file inferred from ACTION] $fileLine\"\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    if ($oldLine -and $fileLine -and $newText) {\n        $isNewFile = ($oldLine.Trim() -eq \"(new file)\")\n        $mutationContent = \"$fileLine`n---`n$(if($isNewFile) { '[NEW_FILE]' } else { $oldLine })`n---`n$newText\"\n        $mutationFile = Join-Path $proposedDir \"$timestamp.mutation\"\n        $mutationContent | Out-File -FilePath $mutationFile -Encoding UTF8\n        Write-Host \"[mutation proposed] $fileLine\"\n        $mutationProposed = $true\n    } else {\n        Write-Host \"[mutation parse failed] old='$oldLine' file='$fileLine' new_len=$($newText.Length)\"\n    }\n}\n\n# Parse OBSERVATION\n$obsMatch    = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?:\\n###|\\nMUTATION)')\n$observation = if ($obsMatch.Success) { $obsMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"Cycle complete.\" }\n\n# Write pulse log\n@\"\n# Pulse: $timestamp\n\n## Applied Mutations\n$appliedInfo\n$(if($rejectedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Rejected: \" + ($rejectedMutations -join '; ') } else { \"\" })\n\n## LLM Response\n$llmResponse\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: $((Get-ChildItem $proposedDir -Filter \"*.mutation\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure).Count)\n- Completed at: $(Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\")\n\"@ | Out-File -FilePath $logFile -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Update pulse history\n$pulseLog = \"$SandboxRoot\\state\\autonomous_pulse.md\"\n$entry    = \"- $timestamp`: $observation$(if($appliedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \" [applied: $($appliedMutations -join ', ')]\" })\"\n$existing = if (Test-Path $pulseLog) { Get-Content $pulseLog -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$updated  = $existing -replace '(## Pulse History)', \"`$1`n$entry\"\n$updated  | Out-File -FilePath $pulseLog -Encoding UTF8\n\n# Git commit\ngit add -A 2>$null\ngit commit -m \"pulse: $timestamp\" 2>$null\n\nWrite-Host \"[sandbox pulse] $timestamp - $observation\"\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774322382924}}
{"type":"message","id":"ef7dded3","parentId":"325c280c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:19:43.828Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fxpiyvi5o59i_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[32;1mFullName                                                                      [0m[32;1m   Length[0m[32;1m LastWriteTime[0m\r\n[32;1m--------                                                                      [0m [32;1m  ------[0m [32;1m-------------[0m\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\autonomous_pulse.md                     34400612 3/23/2026 11:19:39 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 231906.md         5769 3/23/2026 11:19:38 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed\\2026-03-23 231906.mutation     3494 3/23/2026 11:19:38 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.mutation_parse_result.json                       3657 3/23/2026 11:19:38 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.llm_response.txt                                 5549 3/23/2026 11:19:37 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.llm_prompt.txt                                   3622 3/23/2026 11:19:06 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 230908.md         4886 3/23/2026 11:09:43 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\rejected\\2026-03-23 230908.mutation     2659 3/23/2026 11:09:43 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 225907.md         5146 3/23/2026 10:59:38 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\rejected\\2026-03-23 225907.mutation     3638 3/23/2026 10:59:38 PM"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1674,"aggregated":"[32;1mFullName                                                                      [0m[32;1m   Length[0m[32;1m LastWriteTime[0m\r\n[32;1m--------                                                                      [0m [32;1m  ------[0m [32;1m-------------[0m\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\\autonomous_pulse.md                     34400612 3/23/2026 11:19:39 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 231906.md         5769 3/23/2026 11:19:38 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed\\2026-03-23 231906.mutation     3494 3/23/2026 11:19:38 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.mutation_parse_result.json                       3657 3/23/2026 11:19:38 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.llm_response.txt                                 5549 3/23/2026 11:19:37 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.llm_prompt.txt                                   3622 3/23/2026 11:19:06 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 230908.md         4886 3/23/2026 11:09:43 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\rejected\\2026-03-23 230908.mutation     2659 3/23/2026 11:09:43 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 225907.md         5146 3/23/2026 10:59:38 PM\r\nC:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\rejected\\2026-03-23 225907.mutation     3638 3/23/2026 10:59:38 PM","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774322383824}}
{"type":"message","id":"3f06e3c9","parentId":"ef7dded3","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:19:52.426Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see what happened - the pulse script ran and produced output, but the output was mixed/corrupted. Let me read the most recent pulse log file cleanly. The most recent is `pulse_2026-03-23 231906.md`.\n\nWait, looking at the exec output more carefully, I see that the log file output got interleaved with some terminal color codes (the `[32;1m...` stuff) which is ANSI color coding that got mixed into what was being read. \n\nLet me read the actual most recent pulse log directly.","thinkingSignature":"4a248455c83c239b29bcb8a47edf4a137c9055d3b81d5f2b9326cc4f6d3c5025"},{"type":"text","text":"I can see the most recent pulse is `pulse_2026-03-23 231906.md`. Let me read it cleanly.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v4u7wczs24wq_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-23 231906.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":7365,"output":195,"cacheRead":11878,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":19438,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774322383829}}
{"type":"message","id":"d57350ba","parentId":"3f06e3c9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:19:52.439Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_v4u7wczs24wq_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-23 231906\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: TIC (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the state and decide on a concrete action.\r\n\r\nThe current pending task is to run the TIC Experiment:\r\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- [ ] Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- [ ] Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- [ ] Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nThe most concrete, specific next action would be to start implementing the TIC classifier. I should create a script or code that can analyze the pulse logs to classify invariant vs variant content.\r\n\r\nLet me check what files exist in the logs directory and understand the pulse log format first.\r\n\r\nActually, I need to be practical here. The key insight is:\r\n- Causal structure = invariant structure\r\n- A compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\r\n\r\nFor the TIC experiment, I need to:\r\n1. Read recent pulse logs\r\n2. Identify patterns (invariants vs variants)\r\n3. Build a classifier\r\n4. Test prediction\r\n\r\nThe most concrete next action would be to create a TIC experiment script or to actually look at the pulse logs to understand their structure and start building the classifier.\r\n\r\nLet me create a Python script for the TIC classifier that:\r\n1. Reads pulse logs\r\n2. Identifies invariants (things that stay the same across pulses)\r\n3. Classifies content\r\n4. Makes predictions\r\n\r\nThis advances the Phase 1 advancement goal directly.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC experiment is the next critical step - it tests the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis that causal structure equals invariant structure. I need to implement a classifier that can identify invariants across pulse logs and predict next-pulse content.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/TIC/experiment.py` - a TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) classifier that reads pulse logs, identifies invariant vs variant patterns, and tests prediction accuracy against the >70% classification and >60% prediction success criteria.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTIC Experiment: Temporal Invariance Compression Classifier\r\nTests COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis\r\n- Causal structure = Invariant structure\r\n- Compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\n\r\nclass TICClassifier:\r\n    def __init__(self, log_dir=\"logs\"):\r\n        self.log_dir = Path(log_dir)\r\n        self.pulses = []\r\n        self.invariants = {}  # token -> frequency across pulses\r\n        self.variants = {}    # token -> variance measure\r\n        \r\n    def load_pulses(self):\r\n        \"\"\"Load all pulse logs, sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n        pulse_files = sorted(self.log_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"))\r\n        for f in pulse_files:\r\n            with open(f) as fh:\r\n                self.pulses.append({\r\n                    'file': f.name,\r\n                    'content': fh.read()\r\n                })\r\n        return len(self.pulses)\r\n    \r\n    def tokenize(self, text):\r\n        \"\"\"Simple whitespace tokenization.\"\"\"\r\n        return text.split()\r\n    \r\n    def compute_invariants(self, min_freq_pct=80):\r\n        \"\"\"Find tokens that appear in >= min_freq_pct of pulses.\"\"\"\r\n        total = len(self.pulses)\r\n        token_freq = defaultdict(int)\r\n        \r\n        for pulse in self.pulses:\r\n            tokens = set(self.tokenize(pulse['content']))\r\n            for t in tokens:\r\n                token_freq[t] += 1\r\n        \r\n        threshold = (min_freq_pct / 100) * total\r\n        self.invariants = {t: f for t, f in token_freq.items() if f >= threshold}\r\n        return len(self.invariants)\r\n    \r\n    def classify(self, pulse_content):\r\n        \"\"\"Classify tokens as INVARIANT or VARIANT.\"\"\"\r\n        tokens = self.tokenize(pulse_content)\r\n        classified = []\r\n        for t in tokens:\r\n            status = \"INVARIANT\" if t in self.invariants else \"VARIANT\"\r\n            classified.append((t, status))\r\n        return classified\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next(self, current_pulse_idx, lookahead=3):\r\n        \"\"\"Predict tokens likely in next pulse based on invariants.\"\"\"\r\n        if current_pulse_idx + lookahead >= len(self.pulses):\r\n            return None\r\n        next_pulse = self.pulses[current_pulse_idx + lookahead]\r\n        return self.tokenize(next_pulse['content'])\r\n    \r\n    def evaluate(self):\r\n        \"\"\"Run full experiment and return metrics.\"\"\"\r\n        if len(self.pulses) < 5:\r\n            return {\"error\": \"Need at least 5 pulses\"}\r\n        \r\n        # Compute invariants from first 80% of pulses\r\n        split = int(len(self.pulses) * 0.8)\r\n        training_pulses = self.pulses[:split]\r\n        test_pulses = self.pulses[split:]\r\n        \r\n        # Build invariant set from training\r\n        token_freq = defaultdict(int)\r\n        for p in training_pulses:\r\n            for t in set(self.tokenize(p['content'])):\r\n                token_freq[t] += 1\r\n        \r\n        threshold = 0.8 * len(training_pulses)\r\n        training_invariants = {t for t, f in token_freq.items() if f >= threshold}\r\n        \r\n        # Test classification accuracy\r\n        correct = 0\r\n        total = 0\r\n        for p in test_pulses:\r\n            tokens = self.tokenize(p['content'])\r\n            for t in tokens:\r\n                expected = \"INVARIANT\" if t in training_invariants else \"VARIANT\"\r\n                actual = \"INVARIANT\" if t in training_invariants else \"VARIANT\"\r\n                if (t in training_invariants) == (t in training_invariants):\r\n                    correct += \n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-23 23:19:38\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774322392434}}
{"type":"message","id":"fcf7c7ce","parentId":"d57350ba","timestamp":"2026-03-24T03:20:15.952Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pulse log is corrupted - it's mixing script internals with observation content. This is a problem. The pulse script seems to be writing LLM response content directly into the pulse log, but something's going wrong.\n\nLooking at the pulse script, the log is written like:\n```powershell\n@\"\n# Pulse: $timestamp\n\n## Applied Mutations\n...\n## LLM Response\n$llmResponse\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n...\n\"@ | Out-File -FilePath $logFile -Encoding UTF8\n```\n\nThe LLM response itself contains OBSERVATION, ACTION, and MUTATION sections, which then get written to the file. \n\nI think what's happening is the LLM's response is being stored in a file and then read back, but something's going wrong with how it's being written to the pulse log. The LLM response is supposed to be captured from a Python script's output, but it looks like that content is getting corrupted or mixed with other data when it gets written to the log file. Looking at the actual pulse_2026-03-23 231906.md file, I can see the formatting is completely off—the sections are missing their headers and the content is getting truncated partway through. This suggests the file might have been partially written or the output was corrupted during the pulse script execution. I'm realizing the `Get-Content` command with the `-Raw` flag should return the complete file content as a single string, but what I'm seeing in the output appears to be truncated or only partial content. Let me trace through the actual file path that was requested to understand what went wrong.\n\nThe LLM response was only 5549 characters, so it should have been captured completely, but something in how it was written to the pulse log seems to have corrupted the output format. Rather than keep trying to parse this malformed file, I should just report the pulse succeeded with the mutation proposed and flag that the log formatting needs investigation.\n\nLooking at the sandbox state more carefully, I see the pulse logged an observation about the TIC experiment being the next critical step to test the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY hypothesis. The mutation it proposed would create a new file in the research/TIC directory, but the LLM response itself appears truncated—cutting off mid-sentence in the MUTATION block. I can see there was a prior pulse at 23:09 with a rejected mutation (likely due to a failed oldText match), and the most recent pulse from 23:19 successfully proposed a new file mutation for research/TIC/experiment.py. The corrupted log entries appear to be artifacts from terminal color codes bleeding into the file content itself.","thinkingSignature":"7d9c1fbb07b35c68df86d3c07e307b3b5c85dfaf7dd1c1c1ce2a33b4db64fa11"},{"type":"text","text":"The most recent pulse log is corrupted (script internals mixed into it). Let me check the LLM response and mutation parse result for cleaner data.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_skzz2qdsqpl7_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.llm_response.txt"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_skzz2qdsqpl7_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.mutation_parse_result.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8866,"output":647,"cacheRead":11878,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21391,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774322392441}}
